<h1 id=3D"infenterprisebeneficiarymanagementv1-Capability:Createbeneficiary=
"><strong style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);letter-spacing: -0.01em;">Capabil=
ity: Create beneficiary&nbsp;</strong></h1>
<h2 id=3D"infenterprisebeneficiarymanagementv1-POST/beneficiaries">POST /be=
neficiaries</h2>
<p>This endpoint creates a new beneficiary/account as provided in request b=
ody.&nbsp;<br><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);"><span><span class=3D"st=
atus-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">FEB 26</span> The API should en=
force a behaviour of state transition from "ON_HOLD" to "ACTIVE" and reject=
s invalid state transition.&nbsp;</span></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);"><span><span style=3D"color: rgb(25=
5,0,0);"><u><strong>Feb 2026 Changes as part of Divisions:</strong></u></sp=
an><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">&nbsp;DivisionId is included as pa=
rt of the add beneficiary request body so that the same can be persisted in=
 PDP when IROM API gets called from the Beneficiary INF API. Refer to the S=
D here for the sequence flow details:&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"https://conflu=
ence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/SD%3A+Sub-Orgs%28Divisions%29+Channels=
#SD:SubOrgs(Divisions)Channels-Beneficiary-Addbeneficiary" style=3D"" rel=
=3D"nofollow">SD: Sub-Orgs(Divisions) Channels - Beneficiary-Addbeneficiary=
</a></span></span></p>
<p><br></p>
