<h1 id=3D"infenterprisebeneficiarymanagementv1-Capability:Delete/Archivethe=
beneficiary"><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"><strong>Capability: De=
lete/Archive the beneficiary&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"infenterprisebeneficiarymanagementv1-PATCH/beneficiaries/{id}">PA=
TCH /beneficiaries/{id}</h2>
<p>This endpoint deletes the beneficiary/account by changing the status to =
ARCHIVED. If beneficiary is set to ARCHIVED accounts linked to beneficiary =
should be set to ARCHIVED.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);"><span><span class=3D"status-macro =
aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">FEB 26</span> To extend this capability a =
bit further to be "update" status instead of just updating to "ARCHIVE". Th=
e EXP API will trigger update to "ON_HOLD" state or to revert to a previous=
 state. (if downstream DSR call gets any issue)</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);"><span>state validation is expected=
 as per the below scenarios:</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);"><span>expected state flow refers t=
o <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?pa=
geId=3D2088155282#id-05SD:Beneficiaryenhancements&amp;paymenttemplate-State=
TransitionforBeneficiary" rel=3D"nofollow">05- SD: Beneficiary enhancements=
 &amp; payment template - Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise Confluence<=
/a></span></span></p>
<p><br></p>
